Sentencas: Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta, Ce0.8Nd0.2O2-delta and Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-delta samples were prepared by a citrate sol-gel method.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study

Sentencas: Effects of microstructures and oxygen vacancies of the samples on their electrical properties were investigated by X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscope (SEM), in situ Raman spectroscopy and AC impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study

Sentencas: SEM results indicated that larger grains were formed on the Ce0.8Nd0.2O2-delta and Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-delta electrolytes compared to that on the Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study

Sentencas: In situ Raman spectra suggested that the concentration of oxygen vacancies of the Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-delta sample was the highest while that of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta was the lowest.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study

Sentencas: It was found that the difference in the electrical, conductivity for these electrolytes was closely related to the microstructure and oxygen vacancies of the samples.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study

Sentencas: The highest electrical conductivity obtained on the Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-delta sample was ascribed to its larger grain size and higher concentration of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen vacancies on electrical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ electrolyte: An in situ Raman spectroscopic study
